<headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 27 at 6:59AM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...Lake effect snow showers to continue through the morning
commute...
Scattered to numerous snow showers will continue to move across
the area this morning. The potential exists for brief periods of
higher intensity snow showers, resulting in a rapid reduction in
visibilities and a quick accumulation of snow on area roads.
Use caution while driving this morning and allow extra time to
reach your destination. Be prepared for variable road conditions
and lowered visibilities.
IMPACTS...
* Accumulating snow may lead to slippery roads, particularly on
bridges, exit ramps and overpasses.
* Snow showers may cause reductions of visibility to less than
one mile at times. There may be rapid fluctuations of
visibility.
&amp;&amp;
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
* The combination of snow and cold temperatures will result in
localized slippery conditions and variable traffic rates
throughout the county. Motorists are urged to use caution and
account for the variable driving conditions by allowing extra
time.
* Prepare, plan and stay informed. Visit http://go.usa.gov/c7kkP</description>
